<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Complex on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/complex/</link><description>Recent content in Complex on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/complex/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] C++ std::domain_error - sqrt of negative</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/domain-error-sqrt/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/domain-error-sqrt/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="stddomain_error---sqrt-of-negative"&gt;std::domain_error - sqrt of negative&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;std::domain_error&lt;/code&gt; is thrown when &lt;code&gt;std::sqrt&lt;/code&gt; receives a negative argument (for real number output).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: Direct negative
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;double&lt;/span&gt; result &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;sqrt(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;4.0&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// domain error
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Variable becomes negative
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;double&lt;/span&gt; x &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; get_value(); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// may be negative
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;double&lt;/span&gt; root &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;sqrt(x); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// throws if x &amp;lt; 0
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Expression producing negative
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;double&lt;/span&gt; result &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;sqrt(a &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; b); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// if a &amp;lt; b
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-check-before-calling"&gt;Fix 1: Check before calling&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;double&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;safe_sqrt&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;double&lt;/span&gt; x) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (x &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;throw&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;domain_error(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;sqrt of negative&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;sqrt(x);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-use-stdabs"&gt;Fix 2: Use std::abs&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;double&lt;/span&gt; result &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;sqrt(std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;abs(x)); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// always positive
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-use-complex-numbers"&gt;Fix 3: Use complex numbers&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;complex&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;auto&lt;/span&gt; result &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;sqrt(std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;complex&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;double&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;(x, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;));
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/domain-error-pow/"&gt;std::domain_error - pow&lt;/a&gt; — pow domain error.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/domain-error-log/"&gt;std::domain_error - log&lt;/a&gt; — log domain error.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/domain-error-acos/"&gt;std::domain_error - acos&lt;/a&gt; — acos domain error.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Python TypeError — Float and Complex Comparison</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/float-complex-comparison/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/float-complex-comparison/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="typeerror--float-and-complex-comparison"&gt;TypeError — Float and Complex Comparison&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;TypeError&lt;/code&gt; with the message &amp;ldquo;unsupported operand type(s)&amp;rdquo; is raised when you try to compare a &lt;code&gt;float&lt;/code&gt; with a &lt;code&gt;complex&lt;/code&gt; number using comparison operators like &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;=&lt;/code&gt;, or &lt;code&gt;&amp;gt;=&lt;/code&gt;. Complex numbers do not support ordering comparisons in Python.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In Python, complex numbers cannot be ordered because there is no natural way to define &amp;ldquo;greater than&amp;rdquo; or &amp;ldquo;less than&amp;rdquo; for complex numbers. You can check equality (&lt;code&gt;==&lt;/code&gt;) and inequality (&lt;code&gt;!=&lt;/code&gt;) between complex numbers and other numeric types, but you cannot use &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;=&lt;/code&gt;, or &lt;code&gt;&amp;gt;=&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>